# This app does NOT read API keys from environment variables at runtime — keys
# are entered in Settings and stored in the plain-text config file (see README).
#
# This file only documents the token used by the release CI workflow:
#
# GH_TOKEN is provided automatically by GitHub Actions (secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN)
# when publishing releases via electron-builder. You do not need to set it
# locally unless you run `electron-builder --publish` from your machine.
GH_TOKEN=
